Package fr.rphstudio.codingdojo.game.functions

Interface Global

public interface Global
GLOBAL FUNCTIONS
This module contains all the information about the progress of all ships attending the race. It contains also information about the race itself (number o checkpoints, number of max laps to do, number of attendees, ...).
Author:
Romuald GRIGNON

    • getNbRaceCheckPoints

      int getNbRaceCheckPoints()
      Gets the number of checkpoints there in the current track (Code Level #--).
      It means the number of checkpoints to go through in order to validate one complete lap.
      Returns:
      an integer value for the total number of track checkpoints.

    • getShipIndex

      int getShipIndex()
      Gets the index of the current ship (Code Level #--).
      The returned value is between 0 and N-1 (both included), with N the number of ships take from getNbShips().
      Returns:
      an integer value for the current ship index.

    • getNbValidCheckPoints

      int getNbValidCheckPoints()
      Gets the number of checkpoints the current ship has went through (Code Level #--).
      The number returned here will be the sum of all previous validated checkpoints. Dividing this value by the returned value of getNbRaceCheckPoints() will get an approximation of the global race progress (in other words, it will give the floating value of validated laps)
      Returns:
      an integer value for the number of validated checkpoints.

    • getNbCompletedLaps

      int getNbCompletedLaps()
      Gets the number of complete laps the current ship has done (Code Level #--).
      Returns:
      an integer value for the completed laps.

    • getLapPercent

      float getLapPercent()
      Gets a percentage value of the current lap completion by the current ship (Code Level #--).
      Returns:
      a floating value for the lap completion between 0.0 (has not started yet) and 100.0 (has completed a lap, a new lap can begin).

    • getNextCheckPointIndex

      int getNextCheckPointIndex()
      This methods returns the index of the next checkpoint for the current ship (Code Level #--).
      The first checkpoint is visible on the screen with its flag icon .
      Returns:
      an integer value between 0 and N-1 included (with N, a value returned by getNbRaceCheckPoints()).

    • getPreviousCheckPointIndex

      int getPreviousCheckPointIndex()
      This methods returns the index of the previous checkpoint for the current ship (Code Level #9).
      Returns:
      an integer value between 0 and N-1 included (with N, a value returned by getNbRaceCheckPoints()).

    • getSecondCheckPointIndex

      int getSecondCheckPointIndex()
      This methods returns the index of the checkpoint after the next one (for the current ship) (Code Level #9).
      Returns:
      an integer value between 0 and N-1 included (with N, a value returned by getNbRaceCheckPoints()).

    • getNbValidCheckPoints

      int getNbValidCheckPoints​(int index)
      This function is the same than getNbValidCheckPoints() but for a specific ship (Code Level #--).
      The ship index is given in parameter.
      Parameters:
      index - the index of the requested ship. This is an integer value between 0 and N-1, with N the number of ships returned by getNbShips(). Be careful if the index value is out of the range, the result of this function will be for the current ship.
      Returns:
      an integer value. See getNbValidCheckPoints() for details

    • isDisqualified

      boolean isDisqualified​(int index)
      Gets an information about the validity of a specific ship (Code Level #--).
      The ship index is given in parameters. A ship can be disqualified if it does not reach the next checkpoint below a time limit (Common.CHECKPOINT_TIME_LIMIT), or if it goes too far off the screen, or if the ship program calls a function with a forbidden code level. The track valid area is about Common.VALID_LIMIT pixels all around a full HD screen (1920x1080). The corresponding bounds are xmin:Common.MIN_POSX / xmax:Common.MAX_POSX / ymin:Common.MIN_POSY / ymax:Common.MAX_POSY
      Parameters:
      index - the index of the requested ship. This is an integer value between 0 and N-1, with N the number of ships returned by getNbShips(). Be careful if the index value is out of the range, the result of this function will be for the current ship.
      Returns:
      a boolean value that says of the current ship has been disqualified (true) or not (false).
